==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æpɪŋ|-æpɪŋ]]

===Verb form===
'''flapping'''

#[[Present participle]] of '''[[to flap]]'''.

===Adjective===
'''flapping''' (''no [[comparative]] or [[superlative]]'')

#That flaps or flap.
#:''flapping sails''

===Noun===
'''flapping''' (''[[uncountable]]'')

#The action of the verb '''to flap'''.
#(''phonology'') A [[phonological]] process found in many dialects of English, especially [[American English]] and [[Canadian English]], by which [[intervocalic]] /t/ and /d/ surface as the alveolar flap /ɾ/ before an [[unstressed]] [[syllable]], so that words such as "metal" and "medal" are pronounced similarly or identically.
#(''computer networking'') A description of a network interface or device that changes rapidly and repeatedly between online and offline states.
#:''That faulty network card appears to be '''flapping'''.''

